This paper is likely to belong to the Computer Vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with facial makeup transfer, which is a common task in computer vision. Additionally, the use of generative adversarial networks (GANs) is a popular technique in computer vision research.

The paper also involves disentangled representation, which is a technique used in machine learning to separate different factors of variation in data. This suggests that the paper may also belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-category.

The use of GANs and disentangled representation also suggests that the paper may belong to the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category.

The paper may also belong to the Graphics (cs.GR) sub-category as it deals with generating realistic images of faces with makeup.

Finally, the paper may belong to the Multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category as it involves the manipulation of images and the transfer of makeup styles.
